Introduction

Jung Chaeyeon, or simply Chaeyeon, is a South Korean singer, dancer, actress, and model under BH Entertainment. She is best known for being a member of the girl groups DIA and I.O.I.

On September 14, 2015, she debuted as a member of the girl group DIA under MBK Entertainment with the release of their first studio album "Do It Amazing". Shortly after debuting, she and fellow group mate Huihyeon, participated in the survival show Produce 101. Ranking 7th in the finale, she secured her spot in the project girl group I.O.I.

In February 2018, she was announced as one of the new MC for Inkigayo along actor Song Kang and SEVENTEEN's Mingyu. She held that position from February 18, 2018 until her last broadcast on February 3, 2019.
